Bib Tight Guide
Take a closer look at a few of our favorite tights for riding in winter conditions.


Men
Women



Giordana | Assos | Castelli | Pearl Izumi | Garneau | Maloja


















Giordana AV Bib Tight
Giordana’s flagship tight offering is built for riding hard in truly unpleasant winter conditions, courtesy of a slim race cut and highly weather resistant fleece-backed SuperRoubiax fabric. The Cirro S chamois and wicking materials ensure comfort when you’re on the rivet, while a full complement of reflective hits keeps you visible to drivers at dawn and dusk.
Shop Giordana AV Bib Tight




















Assos LL.habuTight_s7
When only the best will do Assos is the obvious choice, and the exemplary Habu bib tights fit that description perfectly. They start with an _s7 level feature package that includes a phenomenal race fit and Assos’s unsurpassed _s7 chamois, and are augmented with a windproof BlasenSchutz front panel to deliver maximum comfort across a wide range of winter conditions.
Shop Assos LL.habuTight_s7






















Castelli Meno 2 Bib Tight
As the sequel to the beloved Meno bib, Castelli’s Meno 2 brings warmth and wind protection for milder conditions along with an impressive feature package—at a surprisingly palatable price. The wind-resistant Thermoflex Core2 front panel shrugs off cool gusts while managing moisture extremely well, making these a training staple for above-freezing temperatures. 
Shop Castelli Meno 2 Bib Tight




















Pearl Izumi P.R.O. Pursuit Cycling Bib Tight
The race-cut P.R.O. Pursuit bib tights benefit from Pearl Izumi’s extensive experience building cycling clothing for challenging conditions. The windproof triple layer softshell material is suitable for cold winter weather, while the raw bib strap edges and pursuit 1:1 chamois all but guarantee rider comfort as the miles add up.
Shop Pearl Izumi P.R.O. Pursuit Cycling Bib Tight




















Louis Garneau Mondo Evo Thermal Bib Tight
Louis Garneau’s home, Quebec, has frightfully cold winters; it’s therefore not surprising that the Mondo Evo bib tights are among the finest race-grade bibs for truly frigid conditions. The heavy windproof fabrics, working in conjunction with HeatMaxx insulation in the abdomen, make these a favorite for riding in sub-freezing weather.
Shop Louis Garneau Mondo Evo Thermal Bib Tight






















Maloja HosfordM Bib Tight
In case you’re not familiar with Maloja, the German brand tends to do things a bit differently. Despite an admittedly non-standard approach, those needing a true deep-winter bib would be wise to consider the the HosfordM bib tights. Built with Lycra WindBlock three-layer fabric and featuring a race-worthy fit, these tights stand out in a crowd in the best possible way.
Shop Maloja HosfordM Bib Tight


Shop All Men's Bib Tights


Giordana | Assos | Castelli | Garneau | Pearl Izumi | Sugoi














Giordana Sosta Tight
For rides driven by enjoyment as much as training, Giordana’s Sosta tights are an easy pick. Designed to be a bit warmer than most race tights, these coffee-ride staples feature Roubaix fabric and a Cirro SW women’s-specific chamois help handle training rides with ease. They’re also incredibly comfortable thanks to a yoga-style waistband, and are presentable-looking off the bike.
Shop Giordana Sosta Tight


















Assos HL.tiburuTight_s7
Arguably the finest all-around women’s tight available, the HL.tiburuTights_s7 are based on Assos’s unrivaled _s7 technology package. They offer the signature “click” fit, as well as the esteemed Lady_s7 chamois wrought from a combination of RX Medium and RX Light materials to maximize your comfort in above-freezing temperatures.
Shop Assos HL.tiburuTight_s7


















Castelli Meno Wind Tight
In spite of the modest asking price, Castelli’s Meno wind tights offer impressive weather protection for milder conditions. The secret is AirFlex Thermal fabric—a windproof material that is unique in its stretchiness, allowing a close to skin fit that shrugs off cold gusts. Factor in the Kiss Air chamois and supportive waistband and it becomes obvious why the Meno has become a firm favorite.
Shop Castelli Meno Wind Tight
























Louis Garneau Course Elite 2 Bib Tights
If truly cold conditions are part of your winter riding routine, look no further than the Course Elite 2 bib tights. Louis Garneau’s Quebec headquarters provided a bitterly cold proving ground for these windproof, highly insulated race bibs. And then there’s the bib strap, which detaches at the front to enable high-speed pit stops—an essential feature for long winter training rides.
Shop Louis Garneau Course Elite 2 Bib Tight




















Pearl Izumi Elite Thermal Cycling Tight
The Elite Thermal tights showcase Pearl Izumi’s mastery of winter clothing despite their modest asking price. The Elite Thermal fleece backed fabric offers outstanding moisture management and a substantial degree of warmth. These versatile winter tights get even better with the Elite 3D chamois, and they’re rounded off by reflective hits to make you more visible on the road.
Shop Pearl Izumi Elite Thermal Cycling Tight




















Sugoi Evolution MidZero Tight
If your list of requirements includes warmth, versatility, and staying visible on the road, the Evolution MidZero tights should be on your radar. The MidZero insulated material features a brushed fleece lining that will keep you comfortable in temperatures approaching freezing, while the large Zap reflective panels at the lower leg ensure that you’ll be seen by passing motorists.  
Shop Sugoi Evolution MidZero Tight


Shop All Women's Bib Tights






